2. CSS


// We need a parent element to use position absolute below with our element we wish to center, so if we need to, we may create a div or
smoething so that we can declare the position as relative
.header{
  position: relative;
}


// Below we set the position to absolute and and the top and left to 50% and then use transform translate to contradict it.
.text-box{
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
